Genitalia . Left phallomere longer than wide; sclerite L4B longer than wide; paa elongated, slightly dilated on the left side of its base, angled approximately 30° from the body axis, afterwards bent to the left, apex simple, directed ventrally ( Fig. 13 D); pda short, broad, flattened, sharply bent 90° to the right, strongly compressed before the apex, the apex also compressed at its base, strongly sclerotized, tapered ( Fig. 16 D); afa elongated, oblique to the body axis ( Fig. 14 D), right margin rugged and sinuous ( Fig. 15 D), posterior apex simple, rugged and strongly sclerotized, anterior apex straight, margins strongly sclerotized, tumid, forming a groove ( Fig. 14 D); loa short, bent to the right ( Fig. 14 D); membrane adjacent to afa pilous ( Fig. 14 D). Right phallomere with the posterior apex rounded; bm short, with a wide expansion ( Fig. 17 D);
pia
short, strongly sclerotized ( Fig. 18 D–19D); pva short, strongly sclerotized, angular apex ( Fig. 19 D); an elongated, apex abruptly rounded ( Fig. 18 D)

Genitalia . Left phallomere longer than wide; sclerite L4B as long as wide; paa elongated, slightly dilated on the left side of its base, angled approximately 30° from the body axis, afterwards curving to the left, apex simple, directed ventrally ( Fig. 13 C). pda short, narrow, flattened, bent to the right, apex strongly sclerotized, tapered ( Fig. 16 C); afa elongated, parallel to the body axis ( Fig. 14 C), right margin smooth and sinuous ( Fig. 15 C), posterior apex tumid, with a projection on the right margin, rugged and sclerotized, anterior apex straight, margins sclerotized and tumid, without forming a groove ( Fig. 14 C); loa short, bent to the right ( Fig. 14 C); membrane adjacent to afa glabrous ( Fig. 14 C). Right phallomere with the posterior apex angular; bm short, with a large expansion near the apex ( Fig. 17 C);
pia
short, strongly sclerotized ( Figs. 18 C–19C); pva short, strongly sclerotized, with a rounded apex ( Fig. 19 C); an elongated, apex abruptly rounded ( Fig. 18 C).
